popt4jlib

Class FiniteLRUFunctionCache

  • java.lang.Object
    • popt4jlib.FiniteLRUFunctionCache
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, FunctionIntf

    public class FiniteLRUFunctionCache
extends java.lang.Object
implements FunctionIntf
    The class is a wrapper for function objects that maintains a finite cache that kicks out the oldest (argument,value) pair that was inserted in the cache if there is no more space available. Whenever the argument is found in the cache, the associated value is returned, otherwise it is computed using the wrapped function, and stored in a ThreadLocal map. Special care is taken to work with double[] objects as keys.

    Title: popt4jlib

    Description: A Parallel Meta-Heuristic Optimization Library in Java

      • eval

        public double eval(java.lang.Object arg,
                   java.util.HashMap unusedParams)
        returns the value stored in the cache if the computation for the arg has been done before, else calls the wrapped function, and stores the key and value pair in the cache, kicking out the oldest existing key-value pair if necessary. If the underlying function throws, +Infinity is recorded in the cache as the argument value.
